{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"tint"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"tint"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Color","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore5ColorV"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"parameters":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The tint "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color"},{"type":"text","text":" to apply."}]}],"name":"tint"}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this method to override the default accent color for this view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Unlike an app’s accent color, which can be overridden by user"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"preference, the tint color is always respected and should be used as a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"way to provide additional meaning to the control."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example shows Answer and Decline buttons with "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/green"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"ty